<para id="element-209">
This example points to an interesting aspect of circular motion. The centripetal acceleration of the cyclist is actually two (2) times that of acceleration due to gravity (g = 10 
<m:math>
<m:mi> m </m:mi>
<m:mo> / </m:mo>
<m:msup>
