<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> i </m:mi>
<m:mo> + </m:mo>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mrow>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
<m:mo> x </m:mo>
<m:mn> 3 </m:mn>
</m:mrow>
<m:mn> 5 </m:mn>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> j </m:mi>

</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-182">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:mo> ⇒ </m:mo> 
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> v </m:mi>
<m:mo> = </m:mo>
<m:mfrac>
<m:mn> 1 </m:mn>
<m:mn> 5 </m:mn>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mo> ( </m:mo>
<m:mn> 4 </m:mn>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> i </m:mi>
<m:mo> + </m:mo>
<m:mn> 3 </m:mn>
<m:mi mathvariant="bold"> j </m:mi>
<m:mo> ) </m:mo>

</m:mtd>
</m:mtr>
</m:mtable>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-183">
Hence, option (a) is correct.
</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
</para>



